Today, a group of faith leaders met with government officials to discuss efforts to welcome and assist Afghan evacuees in the United States. The religious leaders shared the steps they are taking to encourage their communities to get involved, such as donating or volunteering for refugee resettlement agencies and contacting local representatives to support Afghan arrivals. They emphasized the importance of treating everyone with dignity and respect and highlighted the opportunity for Americans to come together across differences. Administration officials highlighted President Biden's commitment to a whole-of-America effort and discussed the launch of the Welcome.US website, which connects organizations and individuals eager to offer support. The religious leaders offered suggestions for collaboration and expanding engagement, and the group pledged to continue working together to help Afghan arrivals thrive in the United States.